{"title_page": "Basovi\u0161\u010da", "text_new": "{{coord|53.106598|23.663435|display=title}}{{short description|Festival of Belarusian alternative and rock music}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{notability|date=June 2014}}\n{{more citations needed|date=June 2014}}\n}}\n\n[[File:Basowiszcza-2007-NRM.JPG|thumb|300px|Basovi\u0161\u010da 2007]] \n[[File:Basowiszcza-2007-audience.JPG|thumb|300px|Basovi\u0161\u010da 2007]]\n[[File:Basowiszcza XXV.jpg|thumb|300px|Basovi\u0161\u010da 2014]]\n\n'''Bas\u00f3vi\u0161\u010da''' (pronounced {{IPA-be|ba\u02c8sov\u02b2i\u0282t\u0282a|}}; Music Festival of Young Belarus) \u2014 the festival of Belarusian alternative and rock music, which is annually conducted by the [[Belarusian Association of Students]] since 1990.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/ru/lyonik-tarasevich-pervoe-basovishche-bolshe-napominalo-studencheskuyu-vstrechu|title=\u041b\u0451\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0422\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447: \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u0435 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0449\u0435\" \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0435 \u043d\u0430\u043f\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u043e \u0441\u0442\u0443\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0443\u044e \u0432\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0443|last=\u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e|first=|date=2014-06-13|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200406055025/https://euroradio.fm/ru/lyonik-tarasevich-pervoe-basovishche-bolshe-napominalo-studencheskuyu-vstrechu|archivedate=2020-04-06|accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/lyonik-tarasevich-pershae-basovishcha-bolsh-nagadvala-studenckuyu-sustrechu|title=\u041b\u0451\u043d\u0456\u043a \u0422\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0432\u0456\u0447: \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0430\u0435 \u201c\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\u201d \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0434\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0443\u0434\u044d\u043d\u0446\u043a\u0443\u044e \u0441\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0440\u044d\u0447\u0443|last=\u0415\u045e\u0440\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0434\u044b\u0451|first=|date=2014-06-12|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200406055449/https://euroradio.fm/lyonik-tarasevich-pershae-basovishcha-bolsh-nagadvala-studenckuyu-sustrechu|archivedate=2020-04-06|accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mpby.ru/news-803.htm|title=\"\u0420\u043e\u043a-\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\" vs. \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\"|last=\u041c\u0456\u043d\u0447\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043a|first=\u0410\u043b\u044f\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439|date=2006-10-30|publisher=mpby.ru|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004165655/http://mpby.ru/news-803.htm|archive-date=2019-10-04|access-date=2019-10-04|work=[[Tuzin.fm]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/yak-na-basovishchy-rykau-tabolich-krama-adpravila-instrumenty-u-pecyarburg|title=\u042f\u043a \u043d\u0430 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u044b\" \u0440\u044b\u043a\u0430\u045e \u0422\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0456\u0447, \u0430 \u041a\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0430 \u0430\u0434\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0456\u043b\u0430 \u0456\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \u045e \u041f\u0435\u0446\u044f\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433|last=\u041c\u0430\u043b\u0456\u043d\u043e\u045e\u0441\u043a\u0456|first=\u0406\u043b\u043b\u044f|date=2013-07-16|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130721025859/http://euroradio.fm/yak-na-basovishchy-rykau-tabolich-krama-adpravila-instrumenty-u-pecyarburg|archivedate=2013-07-21|accessdate=2020-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/ru/kak-na-basovishche-rychal-tabolich-krama-otpravila-instrumenty-v-peterburg|title=\u041a\u0430\u043a \u043d\u0430 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0449\u0435\" \u0440\u044b\u0447\u0430\u043b \u0422\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0447, \u0430 Krama \u043e\u0442\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \u0432 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433|last=\u041c\u0430\u043b\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439|first=\u0418\u043b\u044c\u044f|date=2013-07-16|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160408104428/http://euroradio.fm/ru/kak-na-basovishche-rychal-tabolich-krama-otpravila-instrumenty-v-peterburg|archivedate=2016-04-08|accessdate=2020-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.svaboda.org/a/30051641.html|title=\u041d\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u045e \u043f\u0440\u0430 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\", \u044f\u043a\u0456\u0445 \u043d\u044f \u0441\u043a\u0430\u0436\u0430 \u043d\u0456\u0445\u0442\u043e|last=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0441\u0456\u043c\u044e\u043a|first=\u042f\u043d|date=2019-07-13|website=|publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306191202/https://www.svaboda.org/a/30051641.html|archivedate=2020-03-06|accessdate=2020-03-06}}</ref>\n\nThe festival takes place during two July days in the Borak forest near [[Gmina of Gr\u00f3dek]], [[Poland]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jul/20/belarus-opposition-music-festival-poland-basowiszcza |title='Here we breathe freedom': Basowiszcza festival amplifies Belarus opposition |agency=AFP |date=2015-07-20|newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |language=en |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222174618/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jul/20/belarus-opposition-music-festival-poland-basowiszcza |archivedate=2020-02-22 |access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref> The important part of the festival is the music contest, in which young bands compete for prizes - usually money and rights to record their album for free.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://music.fromby.net/news/bas_nasha.html|title=\"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430-2004\": \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0447\u0430|last=\u041c\u0456\u043d\u0447\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043a|first=\u0410\u043b\u044f\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439|year=2004|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040803011250/http://music.fromby.net/news/bas_nasha.html|archivedate=2004-08-03|accessdate=2019-11-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://generation.by/news6134.html|title=\u0423 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0435 \u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430 \u0441\u0451\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0456\u0447\u0430\u044e\u0446\u044c 28 \u0433\u0443\u0440\u0442\u043e\u045e|last=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043f\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u042f\u0433\u043e\u0440|date=2013-06-04|publisher=Generation.by|language=be|trans-title=28 bands are competing in this year's Basovi\u0161\u010da competition|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031234148/http://generation.by/news6134.html|archive-date=2013-10-31|url-status=live|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=\u041a\u0430\u0440\u043f\u044e\u043a|first=\u0406\u043b\u043e\u043d\u0430|date=2010-07-25|title=\u0422\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u201e\u0437\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0447\u043a\u0456\u201d \u043d\u0430 \u201e\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u044b-2010\u201d \u043d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0432\u044f\u0446\u0456\u043b\u0456\u0441\u044f|url=http://niva.bialystok.pl/issue/2010/30/30_2010.pdf|url-status=live|journal=[[Niva (newspaper)|Niva]]|language=be|volume=|issue=30|pages=3|issn=0546-1960|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318180545/http://niva.bialystok.pl/issue/2010/30/30_2010.pdf|archivedate=2020-03-18|accessdate=2020-03-18|via=}}</ref> Well-known stars of [[Belarus]]ian, [[Rock music in Ukraine|Ukrainian]] and Polish rock-scene usually perform there too.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=113003&lang=ru|title=\u0417\u0432\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430\u043c\u0438 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0449\u0430\" \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438 \"Dzieciuki\": \u0444\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0436|last=\u0420\u0443\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447|first=\u041e\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0430|date=2013-07-23|website=|publisher=[[\u041d\u0430\u0448\u0430 \u041d\u0456\u0432\u0430]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221192936/https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=113003&lang=ru|archivedate=2020-02-21|accessdate=2020-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/ru/basovishcha-kak-novyy-god-mozhet-byt-raznym-no-vse-ravno-ego-otmechaesh|title=\"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\" \u2014 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u041d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u0434: \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0435\u0442 \u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043d\u044b\u043c, \u043d\u043e \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e \u0435\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0442\u043c\u0435\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0448\u044c|last=\u041a\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430|first=\u041c\u0430\u0448\u0430|date=2014-07-22|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=ru|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317190114/https://euroradio.fm/ru/basovishcha-kak-novyy-god-mozhet-byt-raznym-no-vse-ravno-ego-otmechaesh|archivedate=2020-03-17|accessdate=2020-03-17|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/basovishcha-geta-yak-novy-god-mozha-byc-roznym-ale-ty-yago-adznachaesh|title=\"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\" \u2014 \u0433\u044d\u0442\u0430 \u044f\u043a \u041d\u043e\u0432\u044b \u0433\u043e\u0434: \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0430 \u0431\u044b\u0446\u044c \u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u044b\u043c, \u0430\u043b\u0435 \u0442\u044b \u044f\u0433\u043e \u0430\u0434\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0448|last=\u041a\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0456\u043a\u0430\u0432\u0430|first=\u041c\u0430\u0448\u0430|date=2014-07-22|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317190715/https://euroradio.fm/basovishcha-geta-yak-novy-god-mozha-byc-roznym-ale-ty-yago-adznachaesh|archivedate=2020-03-17|accessdate=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===2006===\n17th Basovi\u0161\u010da was held on July 22\u201323, 2006. Contest was on second day. It was the first time when a band from [[Lithuania]], [[IR (band)|IR]], took part in it.\n\n====Contest results====\n'''Winners''':<ref>{{cite news \n |url=http://music.fromby.net/articles.php?id=291 \n |title=\u0412\u044b\u043d\u0456\u043a\u0456 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0443 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430-2006\" (''Results of Basovi\u0161\u010da-2006 contest'') \n |publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]] \n |date=2006-07-23 \n |accessdate=2006-07-30 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070310130202/http://music.fromby.net/articles.php?id=291 \n |archivedate=2007-03-10 \n }}</ref>\n*[[Parason]] - 40 hours of recording in Apollo Studio, and money (1800 zl)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/kudy-znikayuc-peramozhcy-basovishcha|title=\u041a\u0443\u0434\u044b \u0437\u043d\u0456\u043a\u0430\u044e\u0446\u044c \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0436\u0446\u044b \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\"?|last=\u0428\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0446|first=\u041c\u0456\u0440\u0430|date=2013-07-15|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130718092636/http://euroradio.fm/kudy-znikayuc-peramozhcy-basovishcha|archivedate=2013-07-18|accessdate=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/ru/kuda-ischezayut-pobediteli-basovishcha|title=\u041a\u0443\u0434\u0430 \u0438\u0441\u0447\u0435\u0437\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u043f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0438 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0449\u0430\"?|last=\u0428\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0446|first=\u041c\u0438\u0440\u0430|date=2013-07-15|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130721030031/http://euroradio.fm/ru/kuda-ischezayut-pobediteli-basovishcha|archivedate=2013-07-21|accessdate=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n*[[S.D.M. (band)|S.D.M.]] - 25 hours of recording in Studio Rembrandt Radio Bialystok, and money (1200 zl)\n*[[Nevma]] - 1360 zl\n* [[Ludzi \u015bviatla]] - 1000 zl\n*[[Vodar su\u015bviet]] - electric guitar\n\n''Other participants'': [[Band A]], [[Krok (band)|Krok]], [[RoStra]], [[Termin X]], [[Mozart (band)|Mozart]]\n\n====Line up====\n''Friday, July 21'': [[IR (band)|IR]] ([[Lithuania|LT]]), [[5set5]] ([[Poland|PL]]), [[Rima (band)|Rima]] (PL), [[Orchestra Arturo Piazza]] ([[Italy|ITA]]), Ambasadar KROU/[[\u010cyrvonym pa Bie\u0142ym|\u010cpB]] ([[Belarus|BY]]), [[Siddhartha (band)|Siddhartha]] (PL), [[Troitsa]] (BY), [[Zero-85]] (PL), [[Neuro Dubel]] (BY)\n\n''Saturday, July 22'': [[Imprudence]] (BY), [[\u0179miaja]] (BY), [[Indiga (band)|Indiga]] (BY), [[Tav.Mauzer]] (BY), [[Krama (band)|Krama]] (BY), [[Sjel]] (PL), [[B:N:|:B:N:]] (BY), [[Red Emprez]] (PL), [[Drum Ecstasy]] (BY), [[IQ48]] (BY), [[N.R.M.]] (BY)\n\n== Bans ==\nIn 2006, the organizers faced a ban on the concerts of \u201cAdbory\u0161\u010da\u201d (qualifying rounds for \u201cBasovi\u0161\u010da-2006\u201d) in [[Minsk]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mpby.ru/news-671.htm|title=\"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\" - \u0456\u0434\u044d\u0430\u043b\u044f\u0433\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u0431\u044f\u0441\u044c\u043f\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0430\u0435 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0440\u044b\u0435\u043c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430|last=\u0411\u0443\u0434\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439|last2=\u041c\u0456\u043d\u0447\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043a|first2=\u0410\u043b\u044f\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439|date=2006-06-23|publisher=mpby.ru|work=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117144443/http://mpby.ru/news-671.htm|archivedate=2019-11-17|accessdate=2019-11-17}}</ref>\n\n== Criticism ==\nIn 2008 Rock-Princess Kasia Kamockaja as a columnist over at [[naviny.by]] made such a takeaway on the festival, \"\u201eBasovi\u0161\u010da\u201c was conceived not as a festival of Belarusian music in exile, but as a celebration of local [[Bia\u0142ystok]] Belarusians.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://naviny.by/rubrics/opinion/2008/08/17/ic_articles_410_158521|title=\u041a\u0430\u0441\u044f \u041a\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f. \u0428\u041e\u0423-\u0411\u0406\u0417. \u0421\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0434\u0430\u0440\u043d\u044b \u0437 \u0440\u043e\u043a-\u043d-\u0440\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043c?|last=\u041a\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f|first=\u041a\u0430\u0441\u044f|date=2008-08-17|authorlink=Kasia Kamockaja|publisher=[[naviny.by]]|language=be|url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330041249/http://naviny.by/rubrics/opinion/2008/08/17/ic_articles_410_158521/|archivedate=2015-03-30|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref>\n\nOn the pages of [[BelGazeta]], Tat'yana Zamirovskaya wrote in 2007 that the festival \"is the only and oldest music competition in which young Belarusian rock bands can prove themselves and get a very significant prize.\"<ref>{{Cite journal|last=\u0417\u0430\u043c\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f|first=\u0422\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430|date=2007-06-18|title=\u0424\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \"\u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\"|url=http://www.belgazeta.by/ru/2007_06_18/radosti_zhizni/14242/|url-status=live|journal=[[BelGazeta]]|language=ru|volume=24|issue=594|pages=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215074226/http://www.belgazeta.by/ru/2007_06_18/radosti_zhizni/14242/|archivedate=2020-02-15|accessdate=2020-02-15|via=}}</ref> \n\nIn the retrospect of 2010\u20132019 in 2019, Lesha Gorbash from [[34mag]] called the festival \"a [[Mecca]] for [[Rock music in Belarus|Belarusian rock music]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://34mag.net/piarshak/post/belmusic-timeline|title=\u0412\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0432\u0441\u0435: \u0442\u0430\u0439\u043c\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0438 2010\u20132019|last=\u0413\u043e\u0440\u0431\u0430\u0448|first=\u041b\u0435\u0448\u0430|last2=\u041a\u0430\u0448\u043b\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432|first2=\u0410\u043d\u0442\u043e\u043d|date=2019-12-26|website=|last3=palasatka|publisher=[[34mag]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230064444/https://34mag.net/piarshak/post/belmusic-timeline|archivedate=2019-12-30|accessdate=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Basowiszcza}}\n* {{in lang|be|pl}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20060219141945/http://www.basowiszcza.org/ Basovi\u0161\u010da \u2014 the official web-site]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Basovisca}}\n[[Category:Belarusian music]]\n[[Category:Censorship in Belarus]]\n\n\n{{Belarus-stub}}\n{{music-festival-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{coord|53.106598|23.663435|display=title}}{{short description|Festival of Belarusian alternative and rock music}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{notability|date=June 2014}}\n{{more citations needed|date=June 2014}}\n}}\n\n[[File:Basowiszcza-2007-NRM.JPG|thumb|300px|Basovi\u0161\u010da 2007]] \n[[File:Basowiszcza-2007-audience.JPG|thumb|300px|Basovi\u0161\u010da 2007]]\n[[File:Basowiszcza XXV.jpg|thumb|300px|Basovi\u0161\u010da 2014]]\n\n'''Bas\u00f3vi\u0161\u010da''' (pronounced {{IPA-be|ba\u02c8sov\u02b2i\u0282t\u0282a|}}; Music Festival of Young Belarus) \u2014 the festival of Belarusian alternative and rock music, which is annually conducted by the [[Belarusian Association of Students]] since 1990.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mpby.ru/news-803.htm|title=\"\u0420\u043e\u043a-\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\" vs. \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\"|last=\u041c\u0456\u043d\u0447\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043a|first=\u0410\u043b\u044f\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439|date=2006-10-30|publisher=mpby.ru|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004165655/http://mpby.ru/news-803.htm|archive-date=2019-10-04|access-date=2019-10-04|work=[[Tuzin.fm]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/yak-na-basovishchy-rykau-tabolich-krama-adpravila-instrumenty-u-pecyarburg|title=\u042f\u043a \u043d\u0430 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u044b\" \u0440\u044b\u043a\u0430\u045e \u0422\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0456\u0447, \u0430 \u041a\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0430 \u0430\u0434\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0456\u043b\u0430 \u0456\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \u045e \u041f\u0435\u0446\u044f\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433|last=\u041c\u0430\u043b\u0456\u043d\u043e\u045e\u0441\u043a\u0456|first=\u0406\u043b\u043b\u044f|date=2013-07-16|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130721025859/http://euroradio.fm/yak-na-basovishchy-rykau-tabolich-krama-adpravila-instrumenty-u-pecyarburg|archivedate=2013-07-21|accessdate=2020-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/ru/kak-na-basovishche-rychal-tabolich-krama-otpravila-instrumenty-v-peterburg|title=\u041a\u0430\u043a \u043d\u0430 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0449\u0435\" \u0440\u044b\u0447\u0430\u043b \u0422\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0447, \u0430 Krama \u043e\u0442\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \u0432 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433|last=\u041c\u0430\u043b\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439|first=\u0418\u043b\u044c\u044f|date=2013-07-16|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160408104428/http://euroradio.fm/ru/kak-na-basovishche-rychal-tabolich-krama-otpravila-instrumenty-v-peterburg|archivedate=2016-04-08|accessdate=2020-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.svaboda.org/a/30051641.html|title=\u041d\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u045e \u043f\u0440\u0430 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\", \u044f\u043a\u0456\u0445 \u043d\u044f \u0441\u043a\u0430\u0436\u0430 \u043d\u0456\u0445\u0442\u043e|last=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0441\u0456\u043c\u044e\u043a|first=\u042f\u043d|date=2019-07-13|website=|publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306191202/https://www.svaboda.org/a/30051641.html|archivedate=2020-03-06|accessdate=2020-03-06}}</ref>\n\nThe festival takes place during two July days in the Borak forest near [[Gmina of Gr\u00f3dek]], [[Poland]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jul/20/belarus-opposition-music-festival-poland-basowiszcza |title='Here we breathe freedom': Basowiszcza festival amplifies Belarus opposition |agency=AFP |date=2015-07-20|newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |language=en |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222174618/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jul/20/belarus-opposition-music-festival-poland-basowiszcza |archivedate=2020-02-22 |access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref> The important part of the festival is the music contest, in which young bands compete for prizes - usually money and rights to record their album for free.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://music.fromby.net/news/bas_nasha.html|title=\"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430-2004\": \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0447\u0430|last=\u041c\u0456\u043d\u0447\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043a|first=\u0410\u043b\u044f\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439|year=2004|publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040803011250/http://music.fromby.net/news/bas_nasha.html|archivedate=2004-08-03|accessdate=2019-11-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://generation.by/news6134.html|title=\u0423 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0435 \u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430 \u0441\u0451\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0456\u0447\u0430\u044e\u0446\u044c 28 \u0433\u0443\u0440\u0442\u043e\u045e|last=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043f\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u042f\u0433\u043e\u0440|date=2013-06-04|publisher=Generation.by|language=be|trans-title=28 bands are competing in this year's Basovi\u0161\u010da competition|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031234148/http://generation.by/news6134.html|archive-date=2013-10-31|url-status=live|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=\u041a\u0430\u0440\u043f\u044e\u043a|first=\u0406\u043b\u043e\u043d\u0430|date=2010-07-25|title=\u0422\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u201e\u0437\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0447\u043a\u0456\u201d \u043d\u0430 \u201e\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u044b-2010\u201d \u043d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0432\u044f\u0446\u0456\u043b\u0456\u0441\u044f|url=http://niva.bialystok.pl/issue/2010/30/30_2010.pdf|url-status=live|journal=[[Niva (newspaper)|Niva]]|language=be|volume=|issue=30|pages=3|issn=0546-1960|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318180545/http://niva.bialystok.pl/issue/2010/30/30_2010.pdf|archivedate=2020-03-18|accessdate=2020-03-18|via=}}</ref> Well-known stars of [[Belarus]]ian, [[Rock music in Ukraine|Ukrainian]] and Polish rock-scene usually perform there too.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=113003&lang=ru|title=\u0417\u0432\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430\u043c\u0438 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0449\u0430\" \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438 \"Dzieciuki\": \u0444\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0436|last=\u0420\u0443\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447|first=\u041e\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0430|date=2013-07-23|website=|publisher=[[\u041d\u0430\u0448\u0430 \u041d\u0456\u0432\u0430]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221192936/https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=113003&lang=ru|archivedate=2020-02-21|accessdate=2020-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/ru/basovishcha-kak-novyy-god-mozhet-byt-raznym-no-vse-ravno-ego-otmechaesh|title=\"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\" \u2014 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u041d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u0434: \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0435\u0442 \u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043d\u044b\u043c, \u043d\u043e \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e \u0435\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0442\u043c\u0435\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0448\u044c|last=\u041a\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430|first=\u041c\u0430\u0448\u0430|date=2014-07-22|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=ru|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317190114/https://euroradio.fm/ru/basovishcha-kak-novyy-god-mozhet-byt-raznym-no-vse-ravno-ego-otmechaesh|archivedate=2020-03-17|accessdate=2020-03-17|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/basovishcha-geta-yak-novy-god-mozha-byc-roznym-ale-ty-yago-adznachaesh|title=\"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\" \u2014 \u0433\u044d\u0442\u0430 \u044f\u043a \u041d\u043e\u0432\u044b \u0433\u043e\u0434: \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0430 \u0431\u044b\u0446\u044c \u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u044b\u043c, \u0430\u043b\u0435 \u0442\u044b \u044f\u0433\u043e \u0430\u0434\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0448|last=\u041a\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0456\u043a\u0430\u0432\u0430|first=\u041c\u0430\u0448\u0430|date=2014-07-22|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317190715/https://euroradio.fm/basovishcha-geta-yak-novy-god-mozha-byc-roznym-ale-ty-yago-adznachaesh|archivedate=2020-03-17|accessdate=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===2006===\n17th Basovi\u0161\u010da was held on July 22\u201323, 2006. Contest was on second day. It was the first time when a band from [[Lithuania]], [[IR (band)|IR]], took part in it.\n\n====Contest results====\n'''Winners''':<ref>{{cite news \n |url=http://music.fromby.net/articles.php?id=291 \n |title=\u0412\u044b\u043d\u0456\u043a\u0456 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0443 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430-2006\" (''Results of Basovi\u0161\u010da-2006 contest'') \n |publisher=[[Tuzin.fm]] \n |date=2006-07-23 \n |accessdate=2006-07-30 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070310130202/http://music.fromby.net/articles.php?id=291 \n |archivedate=2007-03-10 \n }}</ref>\n*[[Parason]] - 40 hours of recording in Apollo Studio, and money (1800 zl)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/kudy-znikayuc-peramozhcy-basovishcha|title=\u041a\u0443\u0434\u044b \u0437\u043d\u0456\u043a\u0430\u044e\u0446\u044c \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0436\u0446\u044b \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\"?|last=\u0428\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0446|first=\u041c\u0456\u0440\u0430|date=2013-07-15|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130718092636/http://euroradio.fm/kudy-znikayuc-peramozhcy-basovishcha|archivedate=2013-07-18|accessdate=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.fm/ru/kuda-ischezayut-pobediteli-basovishcha|title=\u041a\u0443\u0434\u0430 \u0438\u0441\u0447\u0435\u0437\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u043f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0438 \"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0449\u0430\"?|last=\u0428\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0446|first=\u041c\u0438\u0440\u0430|date=2013-07-15|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130721030031/http://euroradio.fm/ru/kuda-ischezayut-pobediteli-basovishcha|archivedate=2013-07-21|accessdate=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n*[[S.D.M. (band)|S.D.M.]] - 25 hours of recording in Studio Rembrandt Radio Bialystok, and money (1200 zl)\n*[[Nevma]] - 1360 zl\n* [[Ludzi \u015bviatla]] - 1000 zl\n*[[Vodar su\u015bviet]] - electric guitar\n\n''Other participants'': [[Band A]], [[Krok (band)|Krok]], [[RoStra]], [[Termin X]], [[Mozart (band)|Mozart]]\n\n====Line up====\n''Friday, July 21'': [[IR (band)|IR]] ([[Lithuania|LT]]), [[5set5]] ([[Poland|PL]]), [[Rima (band)|Rima]] (PL), [[Orchestra Arturo Piazza]] ([[Italy|ITA]]), Ambasadar KROU/[[\u010cyrvonym pa Bie\u0142ym|\u010cpB]] ([[Belarus|BY]]), [[Siddhartha (band)|Siddhartha]] (PL), [[Troitsa]] (BY), [[Zero-85]] (PL), [[Neuro Dubel]] (BY)\n\n''Saturday, July 22'': [[Imprudence]] (BY), [[\u0179miaja]] (BY), [[Indiga (band)|Indiga]] (BY), [[Tav.Mauzer]] (BY), [[Krama (band)|Krama]] (BY), [[Sjel]] (PL), [[B:N:|:B:N:]] (BY), [[Red Emprez]] (PL), [[Drum Ecstasy]] (BY), [[IQ48]] (BY), [[N.R.M.]] (BY)\n\n== Bans ==\nIn 2006, the organizers faced a ban on the concerts of \u201cAdbory\u0161\u010da\u201d (qualifying rounds for \u201cBasovi\u0161\u010da-2006\u201d) in [[Minsk]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mpby.ru/news-671.htm|title=\"\u0411\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0448\u0447\u0430\" - \u0456\u0434\u044d\u0430\u043b\u044f\u0433\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u0431\u044f\u0441\u044c\u043f\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0430\u0435 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0440\u044b\u0435\u043c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430|last=\u0411\u0443\u0434\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439|last2=\u041c\u0456\u043d\u0447\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043a|first2=\u0410\u043b\u044f\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439|date=2006-06-23|publisher=mpby.ru|work=[[Tuzin.fm]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117144443/http://mpby.ru/news-671.htm|archivedate=2019-11-17|accessdate=2019-11-17}}</ref>\n\n== Criticism ==\nIn 2008 Rock-Princess Kasia Kamockaja as a columnist over at [[naviny.by]] made such a takeaway on the festival, ''\u201c\u201eBasovi\u0161\u010da\u201c was conceived not as a festival of Belarusian music in exile, but as a celebration of local [[Bia\u0142ystok]] Belarusians.\u201d''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://naviny.by/rubrics/opinion/2008/08/17/ic_articles_410_158521|title=\u041a\u0430\u0441\u044f \u041a\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f. \u0428\u041e\u0423-\u0411\u0406\u0417. \u0421\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0434\u0430\u0440\u043d\u044b \u0437 \u0440\u043e\u043a-\u043d-\u0440\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043c?|last=\u041a\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f|first=\u041a\u0430\u0441\u044f|date=2008-08-17|authorlink=Kasia Kamockaja|publisher=[[naviny.by]]|language=be|url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330041249/http://naviny.by/rubrics/opinion/2008/08/17/ic_articles_410_158521/|archivedate=2015-03-30|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref>\n\nOn the pages of [[BelGazeta]], Tat'''\u2019'''yana Zamirovskaya wrote in 2007 that the festival ''\u201cis the only and oldest music competition in which young Belarusian rock bands can prove themselves and get a very significant prize.\u201d''<ref>{{Cite journal|last=\u0417\u0430\u043c\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f|first=\u0422\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430|date=2007-06-18|title=\u0424\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \"\u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\"|url=http://www.belgazeta.by/ru/2007_06_18/radosti_zhizni/14242/|url-status=live|journal=[[BelGazeta]]|language=ru|volume=24|issue=594|pages=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215074226/http://www.belgazeta.by/ru/2007_06_18/radosti_zhizni/14242/|archivedate=2020-02-15|accessdate=2020-02-15|via=}}</ref> \n\nIn the retrospect of 2010\u20132019 in 2019, Lesha Gorbash from [[34mag]] called the festival ''\u201ca [[Mecca]] for [[Rock music in Belarus|Belarusian rock music]].\u201d''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://34mag.net/piarshak/post/belmusic-timeline|title=\u0412\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0432\u0441\u0435: \u0442\u0430\u0439\u043c\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0438 2010\u20132019|last=\u0413\u043e\u0440\u0431\u0430\u0448|first=\u041b\u0435\u0448\u0430|last2=\u041a\u0430\u0448\u043b\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432|first2=\u0410\u043d\u0442\u043e\u043d|date=2019-12-26|website=|last3=palasatka|publisher=[[34mag]]|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230064444/https://34mag.net/piarshak/post/belmusic-timeline|archivedate=2019-12-30|accessdate=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Basowiszcza}}\n* {{in lang|be|pl}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20060219141945/http://www.basowiszcza.org/ Basovi\u0161\u010da \u2014 the official web-site]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Basovisca}}\n[[Category:Belarusian music]]\n[[Category:Censorship in Belarus]]\n\n\n{{Belarus-stub}}\n{{music-festival-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Pr12402", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basovi%C5%A1%C4%8Da"}
{"title_page": "John Billingsley", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor}}\n{{About|the American actor|the British 18th century agriculturalist|John Billingsley (agriculturist)|the voice actor|Beau Billingslea}}{{Infobox person\n| name           = John Billingsley\n| image          = 10.17.09JohnBillingsleyByLuigiNovi.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| caption        = Billingsley at [[Big Apple Convention]], [[Manhattan]], 2009\n| birth_name     =\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1960|5|20}}\n| birth_place    = [[Media, Pennsylvania]], U.S.\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| other_names    =\n| height         =\n| education    = [[Bennington College]] (1982)\n| occupation     = [[Film actor|Film]] and [[television actor]]\n| years_active   = 1988\u2013present\n| website        =\n| spouse         = [[Bonita Friedericy]]\n}}\n\n'''John Billingsley''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|b|\u026a|l|\u026a|\u014b|g|z|l|i}}, born May 20, 1960<ref name=\"http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0082517/?ref_=fn_al_nm_1\">{{cite news |title= This leading-man wannabe is happy to have a TV role in reserve |url= http://articles.latimes.com/2003/sep/07/entertainment/ca-starBILLINGSLEY7 |newspaper= [[Los Angeles Times]] |first= Mark |last= Olsen |date= September 7, 2003 |quote= John Billingsley, 43}}</ref>) is an American actor known for his role as [[Phlox (Star Trek)|Doctor Phlox]] on the television series ''[[Star Trek: Enterprise]]''.\n\n==Early life and education==\nBillingsley was born in [[Media, Pennsylvania]], and subsequently lived in [[Huntsville, Alabama]] and [[Slidell, Louisiana]] before his family settled in [[Weston, Connecticut]].<ref name=OccidentalCollege>[http://www.oxy.edu/theater/guest-artists/guest-artist-bios/john-billingsley \"Theater: Guest Artist Bios: John Billingsley\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113155629/http://www.oxy.edu/theater/guest-artists/guest-artist-bios/john-billingsley |date=2013-11-13 }}. [[Occidental College]]. October 4, 2012.</ref> He graduated from [[Bennington College]] in 1982.<ref>{{cite web |title= Intelligence Cast: John Billingsley |url= http://www.cbs.com/shows/intelligence/cast/214779/ |publisher= [[CBS.com]] |accessdate= August 23, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= John Billingsley: Bio |url= http://www.trademarktalent.com/johnbillingsley/#bio |publisher= Trademark Talent |accessdate= August 23, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Early work===\nBillingsley's first on-screen role was in 1991 as a difficult customer making a return in a customer service training video produced by Nintendo of America.<ref>{{Citation|last=Randy Cornetta|title=Nintendo Training 1991|date=2009-02-03|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WYjgHLFZMa0|accessdate=2017-01-01}}</ref> He made an appearance in \"It Happened in Juneau\", a third-season episode of the TV comedy-drama ''[[Northern Exposure]]'', playing a patient treated by Marilyn. Billingsley made an appearance in ''[[The X-Files]]'' episode entitled \"[[Three of a Kind (The X-Files)|Three of a Kind]]\", playing a friend of [[the Lone Gunmen]] who turns out to be a government spy.\n\n===2000s===\nHe played Dr. John Fallow in a ''[[The West Wing|West Wing]]'' episode that featured the [[Gall\u2013Peters projection]] map ([[Somebody's Going to Emergency, Somebody's Going to Jail|season 2, episode 16]]). He was cast in the role of Professor Miles Ballard in the short-lived television series ''[[The Others (TV series)|The Others]]'' and then as the Denobulan Doctor Phlox in the fifth live action [[Star Trek]] series, ''[[Star Trek: Enterprise]]'', which ran for four seasons. He also played himself in an episode of ''[[Roswell (TV series)|Roswell]]'' that used the ''Enterprise'' set. He also starred in the independent film ''Breathing Hard'' (2000) in the same year. In 2002, he was a guest star in an episode of ''[[Stargate SG-1]]'', playing a scientist who is also a [[Trekkie]], \"worship[ping] at the altar of [[Gene Roddenberry|Roddenberry]]\". Billingsley played a supporting role in the 2003 thriller ''[[Out of Time (2003 film)|Out of Time]]'' starring as medical examiner and best friend to the chief of police played by [[Denzel Washington]].\n\nBillingsley is well known to fans of the series ''[[Cold Case (TV series)|Cold Case]]'' for his guest appearance in the show's second season, playing [[serial killer]] [[List of Cold Case characters#George Marks (John Billingsley)|George Marks]], the only killer on the show to have gotten away with murder. Billingsley would later reprise the role in the season finale, in which Marks was killed. He also appeared as a blunt force victim in the first season of ''[[Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]'', in the episode \"[[The New Person]]\".\n\nBillingsley appeared in the first season of the series ''[[Prison Break]]'' as the mysterious [[Terrence Steadman]], brother of the [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]], whose death is faked to frame [[Lincoln Burrows]] for murder. Soon after, he was cast as a regular on the series ''[[The Nine (TV series)|The Nine]]''. This left him unable to continue his role as Steadman, and he was replaced in the role by [[Jeff Perry (American actor)|Jeff Perry]]. In 2005, he played the voice of Trask in ''Ultimate Spider-Man''. In November 2006, Billingsley portrayed [[William Bradford (Plymouth governor)|William Bradford]] on two episodes of the podcast ''[[The Radio Adventures of Dr. Floyd]]''. In May 2007 he appeared on ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]'' as a blind photographer in the episode, \"In The Dark\". He appeared in the seventh season of ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]'' as a recurring character. On October 8, 2007, he also made a guest appearance on ''[[Journeyman (TV series)|Journeyman]]'' as Alan Platt. Billingsley played Prof. Harry, a biologist, in the 2007 independent science fiction film ''[[The Man from Earth]]''. He also made a guest appearance in an October 2007 episode of ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'', and in 2006 on the spinoff series ''[[CSI: NY]]''.\n\nBillingsley appeared as Jacob Nolston in \"Crash Into Me\", a two-part, fourth-season episode of the TV drama ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''.\n\nBillingsley and his wife have also appeared as themselves on the [[HGTV]] series ''My House Is Worth What?'', in which a real estate expert toured their home and provided commentary for viewers before providing an appraisal.\n\nIn 2008, Billingsley had a supporting role in several episodes of the HBO series ''[[True Blood]]'' as [[coroner]] Mike Spencer. In May of that year, he guest starred as John Harris, the father of the Kiss-Me-Not Killer, in \"Never Tell\", an episode of ''Women's Murder Club''.\n\nHe appeared in the disaster film ''[[2012 (film)|2012]]'', which was released on November 13, 2009, as Professor Frederic West, an American scientist. He subsequently appeared on the ABC series ''[[Scrubs (season 9)|Scrubs]]'' in December 2009.\n\n===2010s===\nIn August 2010, he guest starred in an episode of the [[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT]] series ''[[Leverage (TV series)|Leverage]]'' as Coswell, the head of security at the Boston Museum of Art and Antiquities. In November that year he guest starred as amateur psychic Ellis Mars in \"Red Moon\", an episode of ''[[The Mentalist]]''.\n\nIn February 2011 Billingsley played Gidger in the [[Richard Greenberg]]'s play ''[[The Violet Hour]]'' in Los Angeles.<ref>Anthony, Darin (February 9, 2011). [http://www.lastagetimes.com/2011/02/now-is-the-hour-for-all-good-artists/ \"Now Is the Hour for All Good Artists\"]. ''LA Stage Times''.</ref> In August 2011, Billingsley starred in an episode of the [[USA Network]] drama ''[[Suits (U.S. TV series)|Suits]]'' as the company accountant who is being released for never finishing university.\n\nIn October 2012 Billingsley starred in the film ''[[Trade of Innocents]]'' alongside [[Dermot Mulroney]] and [[Mira Sorvino]].<ref>Savage, Sohpia (August 23, 2012). [http://blogs.indiewire.com/thompsononhollywood/trade-of-innocents-chosen-for-creative-coalitions-spotlight-initiative# \"'Trade of Innocents' Chosen for Creative Coalition's Spotlight Initiative\"]. [[IndieWire]].</ref>\n\nOn February 12, 2013, a web comedy video was released on [[Yahoo! Screens]] under the title \"Forwarders\" that featured Billingsley as an Dr. Alan Cooper, a psychologist and expert on compulsive e-mail forwarding.<ref>[http://screen.yahoo.com/sketchy-forwarders-050000283.html \"Forwarders\"]. [[Yahoo! Screens]]. February 12, 2013.</ref> That same year he completed filming of the independent film ''Red Line''.<ref>[http://www.startrek.com/article/john-billingsley-remembers-dear-doctor \"John Billingsley Remembers Dear Doctor\"]. [[StarTrek.com]]. January 23, 2013.</ref>\n\nOn January 7, 2014, CBS television premiered the science fiction drama ''[[Intelligence (U.S. TV series)|Intelligence]]'', on which Billingsley played Dr. Shenandoah Cassidy, the inventor of an implantable microchip that acts as an interface between a human mind and electronic devices.<ref>[http://www.cbs.com/shows/intelligence/cast/ \"Intelligence Cast\"]. [[CBS]]. Retrieved January 26, 2014.</ref>\n\nIn November 2014, Billingsley guest-starred in the CBS crime drama series, ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]'', playing lawyer Eugene Goodman in the Season 5 episode, \"Ka Hana Malu\".\n\nIn May 2015, Billingsley appeared in the second season of the [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] period drama, ''[[Turn: Washington's Spies]]'', playing Samuel Townsend, father of American Revolutionary spy, [[Robert Townsend (spy)|Robert Townsend]]. He later returned to the role for the third season.\n\nIn July 2017, he appeared as Doctor Ben in the [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] revival of ''[[Twin Peaks (season 3)|Twin Peaks]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nBillingsley is married to fellow actor [[Bonita Friedericy]].<ref name=OccidentalCollege/><ref>[http://www.startrek.com/watch_video/john-billingsley-and-bonita-friedericy-interview-part-2 \"John Billingsley and Bonita Friedericy Interview Part 2\"]. [[startrek.com]]. Retrieved November 13, 2013.</ref><ref>[http://www.startrekcruise.com/star-trek-celebrities/2012-star-trek-cruise-celebrities/john-billingsley \"John Billingsley\"]. Star Trek Cruise. Retrieved November 13, 2013.</ref> She first became interested in him after seeing him perform in a stage production of ''[[Great Expectations]]''.<ref>Winert, Laura (July 28, 2004). [http://www.backstage.com/news/actors-dialogue-bonita-friedericy-john-billingsley/ \"ACTORS' DIALOGUE - Bonita Friedericy & John Billingsley\"]. ''[[Backstage (magazine)|Backstage]]''.</ref> Friedericy appeared with Billingsley in \"[[Regeneration (Star Trek: Enterprise)|Regeneration]]\", a 2003 episode of ''[[Star Trek: Enterprise]]'' in which she played Rooney.<ref>{{cite episode|title=Regeneration|series=[[Star Trek: Enterprise]]|network=[[UPN]]|season=2|number=23|airdate=May 7, 2003}}</ref> The couple have subsequently appeared in other productions together.<ref>[http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/kevin-sorbo-john-billingsley-and-bonita-friedericy-star-in-new-audio-drama-to-benefit-a-world-fit-for-kids-108931509.html \"Kevin Sorbo, John Billingsley and Bonita Friedericy Star in New Audio Drama to Benefit 'A World Fit For Kids'\"]. [[PR Newswire]]. November 18, 2010.</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[The Glass House (2001 film)|The Glass House]]''\n| Driving Instructor\n| \n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[High Crimes]]''\n| Lie Detector Coach\n| \n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Out of Time (2003 film)|Out of Time]]''\n| Chae\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[A Cinderella Story]]''\n| Mr. Rothman\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Room 6]]''\n| Harrison McKendrick\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[The Man from Earth]]''\n| Harry\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[The Last Word (2008 film)|The Last Word]]''\n| Brady\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[2012 (film)|2012]]''\n| Professor Frederick West\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Losing Control]]''\n| Professor Straub\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Sironia]]''\n| Doug\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Trade of Innocents]]''\n| Malcolm Eddery\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Red Line (2013 film)|Red Line]]''\n| Sam\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Madtown (film)|Madtown]]''\n| Lloyd Zane Miller\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[The Man from Earth: Holocene]]''\n| Harry\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Almost Live!]]''\n| [[Bill Gates]]\n| 1 episode\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[NYPD Blue]]''\n| Glenn Farley\n| Episode: [[NYPD Blue (season 5)|\"It Takes a Village\"]]\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[The Practice]]''\n| Revenue Officer Robert Schmidt\n| Episode: \"The Trial\"\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[The X-Files]]''\n| Timothy \"Timmy the Geek\" Landau\n| Episode: \"[[Three of a Kind (The X-Files)|Three of a Kind]]\"\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[The West Wing]]''\n| Dr. John Fallow\n| Episode: [[List of The West Wing episodes#ep38|\"Somebody's Going to Emergency, Somebody's Going to Jail\"]]\n|-\n| 2001-2005\n| ''[[Star Trek: Enterprise]]''\n| Dr. [[Phlox (Star Trek)|Phlox]]\n| 91 episodes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[NYPD Blue]]''\n| Ryan Lipe\n| Episodes: [[NYPD Blue (season 9)#ep186|\"Oh, Mama\"]] and [[NYPD Blue (season 9)#ep191|\"Gypsy Woe\u2019s Me\"]]\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Stargate SG-1]]''\n| Dr. Simon Coombs\n| Episode: [[List of Stargate SG-1 episodes#ep118|\"The Other Guys\"]]\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Duck Dodgers (TV series)|Duck Dodgers]]''\n|Dr. Psy-Q Hi (voice)\n|2 episodes\n|-\n|2004 & 2005   \n|''[[Cold Case]]''\n|George Marks\n|2 episodes: [[List_of_Cold_Case_episodes#Season_2_(2004%E2%80%9305)|Mind Hunters]], [[List_of_Cold_Case_episodes#Season_2_(2004%E2%80%9305)|The Woods]]\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Prison Break]]''\n| Terrence Steadman\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n|2006\n|''[[The Closer]]''\n|Tom Newman\n|Episode: \"[[List of The Closer episodes#Season 2 (2006)|Aftertaste]]\"\n|-\n|2006-2007\n|''[[The Nine (TV serie